  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Gender in Agriculture Project in Chakai Block of Jamui District, Bihar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Develop demo plots &amp;amp; field trials for all 505 Farming households (505 women+504 men from 9 villages) on cereals, pulses, and vegetables.
- Provide Pre &amp;amp; Post harvest farm tools &amp;amp; vegetable tool kit to 505 Farming households.
- Conduct one training for Self-help Group (SHG) leaders on centralized procurement of inputs, distribution of agricultural inputs
- Construction of 10 ring base intake wells constructed for 10 LIs to ensure year-round irrigation support with labor contribution from beneficiaries
- Conduct one gender sensitization training for 3 days duration to educate on gender analysis, the development of Behavioral Change Communication (BCC) tools and their application</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Dalits, Women, Indigenous People</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Goal: Increased production for 500 farming households in Chakai block of District Jamui, in Bihar, India to provide year-round household income to meet food and basic needs after 2 years.

Objective 1. To increase production of cereals by 60% (rice and wheat), pulses to 50% and to introduce vegetable cultivation for 500 farming households through improved agriculture practices, inputs and technology in 2 years of project period.
Objective 2. Irrigation benefits provided to 500 farming households to cover 15 decimals of land by each irrigation structure, through creation of small scale water harvesting structures and making provision of equipments to transport water to the field.
Objective 3. To improve understanding for 500 women and their spouses on improved gender roles in agriculture by conducting training and BCC sessions.</narrative>
  </description>
